# Workspace Hygiene

This project lives on OneDrive. Build artifacts dramatically slow down sync. Always keep the workspace lean.

## After any build or `npm install`, delete these immediately

- `dist/` — Astro build output (regenerate with `npm run build`)
- `node_modules/` — npm packages (regenerate with `npm install`)
- `.vercel/` — Vercel local cache (auto-regenerates on deploy)
- `.astro/` — Astro cache (auto-regenerates on next build)

## After any script run, delete these

- `*.log` files in the project root
- `*.log` files in `_research/`

## Never commit these

All of the above are already in `.gitignore`. Do not stage or commit them under any circumstances.

## Restoring when needed for a task

Only restore these folders if the current task explicitly requires a local build or install:

```bash
npm install          # restores node_modules/
npm run build        # restores dist/
```

Delete them again once the task is complete.
